grievance /ˈɡriːvəns/

(grievances) 

1. N-VAR If you have a grievance about something that has happened or been done, you believe that it was unfair. 委屈; 不满 

例： They had a legitimate grievance. 他们的委屈是合乎情理的。 

例： The main grievance of the drivers is the imposition of higher fees for driving licences. 司机们的主要不满是加诸在驾驶执照上的更高的费用。

